features.additionalValue: Additional repayments and Early Repayment Adjustment
features.additionalInfo: Unlimited additional repayments and early repayments (discharge fee may apply) when on variable rate home loans. You may make up to $10,000 of additional payments a year on fixed rate loans. Early loan payout on a fixed rate loan may result in break costs being charged.

eligibility.additionalValue: You must be an Australian citizen or permanent Australian resident that resides in Australia.
eligibility.additionalInfo: You must be an Australian citizen or permanent Australian resident that resides in Australia.
To apply you need to be 18 years of age or over.

fees.name: Additional progress payment fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable for every progress payment made after the 5 progress payments covered in the construction loan fee.

fees.name: Additional valuation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable for any additional valuation required as part of the loan settlement process. Covers valuation for a residential property valued up to $1.5M. Please note: Valuation for any residential property with an expected value above $1.5M will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Audit request fee
fees.additionalInfo: $30 per hour (min charge $30). Charged when you request us to provide a written confirmation of your financial accounts with Australian Unity.

fees.name: Break cost fee
fees.additionalInfo:
Applicable to fixed home loans only. The purpose of applying the break cost is to compensate us for the loss which we incur as a result of the effective termination of your contract with us (reasons may include but are not limited to the loan being paid in full before the fixed rate period or making additional payments above $10,000 in any 12 month period). 

For more information refer to the Loan Fee Schedule

fees.name: Change of security fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you wish to change security against your Home Loan with another security that is currently mortgaged to Australian Unity. If discharge of existing security is required, the discharge of mortgage fee will also be payable

fees.name: Construction loan fee
fees.additionalInfo: This fee includes property valuations at up to 5 stages of construction and up to 5 progress payments. Additional valuations or progress payments will be charged the standard published fees as listed in the Loan Fee Schedule.

fees.name: Discharge fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the security on your property is released. This fee covers our costs of preparing the necessary documentation to allow the discharge of your mortgage or other security type. Statutory government registration fees will also apply. Fee does not include settlement agent fees in non-CBD locations, which will be charged additionally as per cost to us.

fees.name: Documentation search fee
fees.additionalInfo: $30 per hour (min charge $15). Charged when you request us to search and/or retrieve voucher/s or other documentation connected to your accounts with Australian Unity.

fees.name: Fixed interest rate lock fee
fees.additionalInfo: 0.15% of the approved fixed loan amount with a minimum fee of $499. The fixed interest rate will be locked (held) for a Rate Lock Period of 90 days from the date we receive the fixed interest rate lock request and is not available after this 90 days Rate Lock Period has ended. The Fixed Interest Rate Lock Fee will not be charged if settlement does not proceed.

fees.name: Interest type switch fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you request to change your loan interest rate type e.g. Interest Only to Principal and Interest or vice versa and/or Variable to Fixed Interest Rate or vice versa. This fee is not charged on package loans.Please note: Penalties apply if breaking out of fixed rate option prior to expiry of existing fixed rate period. Refer to Break Cost Fee in the Loan Fee Schedule for more information.

fees.name: Lenders mortgage insurance
fees.additionalInfo: Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI) is an insurance policy that protect Australian Unity Bank from any loss if a borrower defaults on their home loan. It does not protect the borrower. It is a one-off, non-refundable, non-transferrable premium that’s added to your home loan. You may be charged LMI if you borrow more than 80% of the value of your property.

fees.name: Loan establishment fee
fees.additionalInfo: This fee is applicable to new, non package loans. This fee covers the cost of property valuation (for one residential property up to $1.5M) and preparation of the loan documents. Please note: Valuation for any residential property with an expected value above $1.5M will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Loan re-documentation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if the loan documents need to be reprepared due to a change in requirements by the customer. This fee also applies should you not proceed with the loan after the new loan contract is prepared.

fees.name: Loan restructure fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the loan requires restructuring e.g. when a loan is changed from having two account holders to one account holder. Discharge of mortgage fee will also apply if a discharge and lodgement of a new mortgage are required.

fees.name: Loan top up fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when additional funds are requested under an existing mortgage. This fee covers administration costs where there is no change to the security or borrowers. Please note: Full valuation required for a loan top up will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Preparation of deed of priority
fees.additionalInfo: Payable per occurrence of preparation of deed of priority.

fees.name: Product switch fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable to cover associated administrative costs when switching between loan products.

fees.name: Self-serve redraw
fees.additionalInfo: A redraw facility allows you to access additional payments that you’ve made on your home loan. When you do this yourself via Internet Banking or the Mobile banking app, there is no fee. Minimum $500.

fees.name: Staff assisted redraw fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when a redraw request is manually performed by a staff member.

fees.name: Title/documentation production fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable per occurrence of title production request. Statutory government fees will also apply.

fees.name: Change of security fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when you wish to change security against your Home Loan with another security that is currently mortgaged to Australian Unity. If discharge of existing security is required, the discharge of mortgage fee will also be payable

fees.name: Construction loan fee
fees.additionalInfo: This fee includes property valuations at up to 5 stages of construction and up to 5 progress payments. Additional valuations or progress payments will be charged the standard published fees as listed in the Loan Fee Schedule.

fees.name: Discharge fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the security on your property is released. This fee covers our costs of preparing the necessary documentation to allow the discharge of your mortgage or other security type. Statutory government registration fees will also apply. Fee does not include settlement agent fees in non-CBD locations, which will be charged additionally as per cost to us.

fees.name: Documentation search fee
fees.additionalInfo: $30 per hour (min charge $15). Charged when you request us to search and/or retrieve voucher/s or other documentation connected to your accounts with Australian Unity.

fees.name: Fixed interest rate lock fee
fees.additionalInfo: 0.15% of the approved fixed loan amount with a minimum fee of $499. The fixed interest rate will be locked (held) for a Rate Lock Period of 90 days from the date we receive the fixed interest rate lock request and is not available after this 90 days Rate Lock Period has ended. The Fixed Interest Rate Lock Fee will not be charged if settlement does not proceed.

fees.name: Lenders mortgage insurance
fees.additionalInfo: Lenders Mortgage Insurance (LMI) is an insurance policy that protect Australian Unity Bank from any loss if a borrower defaults on their home loan. It does not protect the borrower. It is a one-off, non-refundable, non-transferrable premium that’s added to your home loan. You may be charged LMI if you borrow more than 80% of the value of your property.

fees.name: Loan re-documentation fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable if the loan documents need to be reprepared due to a change in requirements by the customer. This fee also applies should you not proceed with the loan after the new loan contract is prepared.

fees.name: Loan restructure fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when the loan requires restructuring e.g. when a loan is changed from having two account holders to one account holder. Discharge of mortgage fee will also apply if a discharge and lodgement of a new mortgage are required.

fees.name: Loan top up fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when additional funds are requested under an existing mortgage. This fee covers administration costs where there is no change to the security or borrowers. Please note: Full valuation required for a loan top up will be charged as per the cost to us.

fees.name: Preparation of deed of priority
fees.additionalInfo: Payable per occurrence of preparation of deed of priority.

fees.name: Product switch fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable to cover associated administrative costs when switching between loan products.

fees.name: Self-serve redraw
fees.additionalInfo: A redraw facility allows you to access additional payments that you’ve made on your home loan. When you do this yourself via Internet Banking or the Mobile banking app, there is no fee. Minimum $500.

fees.name: Staff assisted redraw fee
fees.additionalInfo: Payable when a redraw request is manually performed by a staff member.

fees.name: Title/documentation production fee
